modules.description: Measures elapsed time in nanoseconds and optionally returns the monotonic time period. Works with 64-bit integers and optional values. Useful for benchmarking code execution or tracking time intervals in systems programming.

This module tracks and advances a simulated monotonic time value. It provides functions to get the current time (`now`), increment the time by one unit (`tick`), and advance it by a specified amount (`tick_for`). It is used in testing to simulate time progression without relying on real-time delays.
